                <h1>Skull and Crossbones: The Symbol of Danger and Rebellion</h1>
                <p>The skull and crossbones symbol, often associated with danger and toxicity, originates from piracy and signifies a warning. It represents the perils of poison, death, and sometimes rebellion. Its striking imagery has become an emblem in various contexts, from caution signs on hazardous materials to pop culture references in fashion and art.</p>
